  m_Name: GeneralTips
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  strings:
  - Alt-click while holding a health analyzer to get a full report on the body part
    you're targeting, including information on the organs inside it.
  - Body parts can be dismembered and burnt using the right weapons and tools.
  - Your lungs can bleed from the inside, forcing you to drown in your own blood.
  - Security officers can heal a small amount of brute damage by eating donuts.
  - Lizards have thicker skins that allow them to have more chances against attacks
    that might otherwise be deadily for other races.
  - Play as an Assistant as your first time. Nobody will expect anything from you
    and you'll have a great chance to learn the game.
  - A Proto-Kinetic Accelerator (PKA) can destroy walls.
  - Kick back and relax at the bar or dorms and play some card games or Dungeons
    & Dragons with your other crewmates.
  - Killing your crewmates for no reason is the fastest way upset a mob -- and server
    admins.
  - As the quartermaster, it is your job to make sure that all departments are well
    supplied. However, never be afraid of denying some requests. Seriously, does
    the clown really need ten costume crates?
  - Plants need water, nutrients and care. Keep an eye on them and make sure they
    grow up healthy.
  - You can use a crowbar to open airlocks and unpowered doors.
  - Drinking too much alcohol is a guaranteed way to build up toxin damage and destroy
    your liver.
  - Facehuggers cannot tear off large facial obstructions, like hardsuit helmets,
    that are obscuring your head.
  - Running makes you hungry faster.
  - Hardsuits slow you down.
  - In space, no one can hear you scream.
  - Ore boxes automatically collect minerals when pulled over them.
  - Never take pills labeled as "Happy Pills".
  - A crewmate who's competent enough to do their job is an antagonist's worst nightmare.
  - Perform CPR to revive a dying crewmate by changing your intent to <color=green>Help</color>,
    then targeting where their heart is at.
  - Snacks from vending machines aren't fulfilling, but they're good enough to keep
    you running for a few more minutes.
  - Say <i>"Come Ian!"</i> near Ian the dog to make him come to you.
  - A handcuffed or restrained player cannot move freely if you grab or pull them.
  - If you die, there's always a chance you can respawn as another character or play
    as a ghost role.
  - Touching a light bulb without gloves will cause burn damage to your hand.
  - Letters, manifests and documents can be printed from a printer.
  - Clowns who take off their outfit as a sort of meta-disguise are the most dishonorable
    of all traitors, but there's no denying the practice can work wonders and catch
    even veterans off-guard.
  - There are plenty of ways to gib your victims on the station, however many are
    job specific.
  - The gravitational singularity will emit electromagnetic pulses, which will fry
    nearby devices, including cameras and headsets.
  - Your role as a detective is only loosely related to law enforcement. You're better
    suited for information gathering rather than arrests.
  - Flashlights emit light even when in your pocket.
  - Running in the halls can be dangerous if you want to walk and slow down press
    C or click the shoe icon in the bottom right corner. Walking will also prevent
    you from slipping on wet spots.
  - Need to go AFK? If you can try to make your way to one of the rooms in the dorms.
    It it is a safe place to take a little nap.
  - Want to contribute but don't know want to code? The Wiki is always looking for
    new editors to write up or edit some articles.
  - Want to Mime or spice up your actions? Press \ to open the emote menu for a list
    of  different emotes or put * in front of what you say to make it a action.
  - Found a bug or issue? Reporting it on the discord or in the GitHub helps out
    a lot.
